name: David Stone
text: We found out that this waterfall is on private property and has no public access, do not bother trying to find it. You will be blocked by a gate.

name: John “Slaprock for real” Mcree
text: If you like meth and getting shot at go ahead and look forcthis palce

name: Kenneth Barnett
text: What a great Falls to visit short hike into it

name: John Caleb
text: Gorgeous Falls and a wonderful area to explore, although the trail is not marked very well, so it would be best to take along someone who has been before. There is also not a trailhead marker so you have to look for the path on the roadside.

name: Jeff Doby
text: Beautiful hike through the woods

name: Amy Hall
text: Great hike not that difficult beautiful falls

name: Carolann McFry
text: OMG loved it

name: Kimmie Q
text: Went out searching waterfalls. This is ANOTHER that we did not find a waterfall.

name: Stephen Slater
text: No waterfall here.

name: Dennis Carmichael
text: Couldn't find it

name: Cynthia Frazier
text: Extremely difficult to get down to this fall. There is no trail. You must climb over rocks and through briars and poison ivy. But wow...it was worth it!! Gorgeous place!

name: Adventure Queen
text: High falls is beautiful and the area is very relaxing. The walk to the falls is short. There is a beautiful bridge over the creek and plenty of places to enjoy a picnic. There are nice restrooms available.

name: terese c
text: My daughter and I really enjoyed ourselves!

name: Edward Sazonov
text: Quite beautiful when the water is high. In dry weather the waterfall disappears. For those who like to hike, the trail goes on both sides of the waterfall. Arrive from one side, cross the creek and continue to another side. Be ready to climb!

name: Regis Glover
text: Beautiful hike.

name: Matthew James
text: Such a great place with a short hike.

name: Bill Tiemann
text: The hike in and out is steep and over some fairly treacherous terrain but it's worth it. On this occasion it hadn't rained for several days so the flow was kind of underwhelming. Still all things considered it was a good hike.

name: Slemian Sefyan
text: Wasn't any water

name: Amber Pryde
text: Great hike! This one is a tough one for the novice hiker. Be ready to climb! Not a long hike, but getting down to the falls has a lot of rocks. Recommend going in on the blue trail across the water then out on the white. Don't forget to stop at the look out 👀. When it's rained everything is slippery so I recommend hiking boots and water. No tennis shoe friendly. Glad we stopped here, this is you don't want to miss.

name: Ann Whitaker
text: Beautiful but seasonal falls. If it has been dry so will the falls be. Very steep around the falls, wear hiking boots, or anything else with support to ankles.

name: John Cottingham
text: Beautiful place! Although the hike in is short 1/4 mile, the elevation drop is steep and rocky. It’s deceiving because it’s all downhill to the falls. The real work starts on the way out. Since it’s in a canyon, there is little breeze and in the summer pretty hot. Remember to bring water.

name: Xyan Aguilar
text: Just a heads up, you have to pay (cash only, they have an ATM that barely works) in order to get in. Definitely the first park I've been to that requires payment to hike.

name: Tia Soto-Navarro
text: Very, very steep trail. No real clear trail marked to get down to it. If there has been no rain, there will be no fall...spring fed, maybe a trickle.

name: Tina Lockhart
text: Beautiful waterfall, pretty steep hike but worth it

name: James C
text: Nice view trail could use some repairs

name: KML SINGH
text: Take white trail from main parking nearby and it's just 200ft from there

name: Michelle McKenzie Mackintosh
text: Beautiful!

name: jonathan dryer
text: This a not so well know waterfall but it's  pretty cool place. The hike is straight up hill about .25 mile and there is a cave where you can walk behind waterfall and best day to check this one out is after a good rain. The water flow will be greater

name: The Bearded Man-Drenaline
text: One of my favorite places to spend the day, hiking, climbing, and exploring and just being alone with The Creator of the Universe, YHWH, redeemed by His Son Yahusha ha Mashiach(Jesus the Messiah)🙌

name: Seth Eden
text: This place is amazing!! A bit of a challenge with the steep cliffs and a little basic rock climbing. The falls are dissappointing to say the least. It was more like someone left their garden hose on. The problem with our trip was the cult that was holding violent angry non-Christian spiritual rituals to the left side down the trail further. It was clear they had left fresh flowers for the spirits along the sides of the cliffs. We wanted to continue exploring the trail but angry violent spiritual cult rituals are not family friendly so we turned around and left.

name: Sunshine Knighton
text: Steep hike and climb to the falls. Beautiful spot, but people tend to leave much trash at the trailhead. There are no trail blazes but simple to find. Moderate to difficult trail, but worth it.

name: Drone It 1969
text: Hiked about 1/2 mile then had to rock climb.  Nope didn't make it

name: Jeff Doby
text: A short up hill hike for a beautiful waterfall worth it for sure

name: Loretta B
text: This is classified as a moderate hiking trail that leads up to a beautiful waterfall!

name: Sharon Kilzer
text: This "roadside" fall is worth the short trek up to see it. It can be a strenuous hike up as there are roots and rocks strewn everywhere.

name: Jill Johnson
text: Love this waterfall. We enjoyed the hike up to the falls. As with many of these beautiful falls the littering is out of control. I found some empty Walmart bags and cleaned up what I could. The things that were there could have easily been put in a pocket.  Please help keep this fall clean. For those of us that respect The Land please take a bag or 2 and some rubber gloves and help care for this Beautiful land. Once again I Love all the beautiful things that Mother Nature has given us and much respect.

name: Vyktorya Bryant
text: Nearly made it to the top,my kids go climbing w/me,some beautiful views.

name: daddy catty
text: Went there after a 3 day rain. It was the most awesome thing I've ever seen. You climb up the rocks and it looks like the water is coming out of the sky. Just beautiful.

name: jsks shdj
text: Its good for hiking

name: Shera Woodruff
text: Beautiful

name: Kartr Higgins
text: Its a steep hike, but not to far. Beautiful waterfalls!

name: Danny Cain
text: Well worth the hike

name: Colie Farmer
text: Went the other day, didn’t see a waterfall or anything. Just a bunch of rocks

name: Asia Hutchinson
text: This is named after our family.

name: Frances Dobbins
text: Beautiful place
